Patient: What foods should I eat to help manage my heart failure?
Educator: Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, lean proteins, and low-fat dairy. 
Patient: Are there any specific foods I should avoid?
Educator: Limit salt, sugar, and saturated fats to help your heart stay healthy. 
Patient: Can I still enjoy my favorite cultural dishes?
Educator: Yes, try making them healthier by using less salt and oil. 
Patient: How can I make sure I'm eating the right foods for my heart?
Educator: Keep a food journal and track your meals to stay on top of your diet. 
Patient: Thank you for the food recommendations, I feel more confident now.
Educator: You're welcome! Remember, small changes can make a big difference in your heart health.